  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oil in a deep frying pan to 350°F (180°C).",
    "Lay a wonton wrapper on a clean surface and place a tablespoon of the lamb mixture in the center of the wrapper.",
    "Brush the edges of the wrapper with water.",
    "Fold the bottom half of the wrapper over the filling, then fold in the sides and roll up the wrapper to form a tight cylinder.",
    "Repeat with the remaining wrappers and filling.",
    "When the oil is hot, carefully place a few egg rolls into the oil and fry until golden brown, about 3-4 minutes per side.",
    "Remove the egg rolls from the oil with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.",
    "Serve the egg rolls hot with a dollop of yogurt sauce (see below)."
  ],
